    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1539"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1539">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.48/18.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the American Red
                            Cross</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">National Headquarters</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your letter of August 28, 1912,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d1539fn1">Not printed.</note> suggesting that the Red Cross
                    could greatly alleviate the suffering which is bound to follow the revolutionary
                    disturbances by making an additional appropriation of $2,000 worth of corn and
                    beans to be distributed in the same manner as the supplies so far sent to
                    Nicaragua, I have <pb facs="1246" n="1130" xml:id="pg_1130"/> the honor to
                    advise you that the Executive Committee hereby authorizes the expenditure of
                    $1,000 additional by the State Department for the above purpose.</p>
                <p>As in the case of the former appropriation of $1,000, a check payable to the
                    Secretary of State will be delivered to you upon the receipt of an account
                    showing the exact amount of the expenditure.</p>
                <p>The Red Cross very much regrets that its limited funds will not permit a larger
                    appropriation at this time.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles L. Magee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
